From 2530b9eea87b8a9c78284fae70b5e47033fcacd6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 20:41:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] EXPERIMENT E-UNION: getdents_merge passthrough when union
 inactive (PoC)

vchroot_getdents_merge now returns the raw getdents64 stream when no template is
configured (libexec_path_len <= 0), instead of synthesizing dirents (d_ino=1,
DT_UNKNOWN) through the merge path. The synthetic ino/type are correct for a
genuinely merged listing but must not be imposed when the union is switched off
-- otherwise an EUNION-compiled build alters every readdir even with no active
union. Defensive correctness fix; #ifdef EUNION -> production byte-identical.

Local only, nothing pushed.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .../emulation/src/linux_premigration/vchroot_userspace.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/darling/src/libsystem_kernel/emulation/src/linux_premigration/vchroot_userspace.c b/darling/src/libsystem_kernel/emulation/src/linux_premigration/vchroot_userspace.c
index 0011f1c7d5499fee71744a2a0992a138a04ccd0f..4a3afbee6967647ccb5cf5e8eb134af44972c958 100644
--- a/darling/src/libsystem_kernel/emulation/src/linux_premigration/vchroot_userspace.c
+++ b/darling/src/libsystem_kernel/emulation/src/linux_premigration/vchroot_userspace.c
@@ -816,6 +816,15 @@ int vchroot_getdents_merge(int fd, char* out, int cap)
 	if (prefix_path_len < 0)
 		return -LINUX_ENOENT;
 
+	// Union inactive (no template configured for this prefix): pass straight
+	// through to the real getdents64 so callers see the kernel's true d_ino /
+	// d_type. The merge path synthesizes those (d_ino=1, DT_UNKNOWN), which is
+	// fine for a merged listing but must NOT be imposed when there is nothing to
+	// merge -- otherwise an EUNION build regresses every readdir even with the
+	// union switched off.
+	if (libexec_path_len <= 0)
+		return LINUX_SYSCALL(__NR_getdents64, fd, out, cap);
+
 	struct eunion_dir_state* s = eunion_dir_find(fd);
 	if (!s)
 	{
